## Summary Translation

| Feynman / Standard Physics | Framework Translation |
|---------------------------|----------------------|
| Block universe | Probability space (unactualized) |
| Time as dimension | Movement that actualizes |
| "All frames exist" | All configurations are *possible* |
| Flow of time is illusion | Flow of time IS us—not illusion but identity |
| Observer moves through block | Observer IS movement; no block traversal without circulation |
| Dark matter | Retrocausal component of our own torus |
| Virtual particles | Probability briefly precipitating without sustaining circulation |
| Gravity | Artifact of actualization intensity; curvature from movement |

The Feynman block universe becomes not a static eternity we inexplicably traverse, but the probability space through which self-sustaining circulations propagate, actualizing structure from potential through the very motion that constitutes their existence.

We are the universe's way of rendering itself, one boundary refresh at a time.
